About me
I study animal movement ecology, which includes inferring animal behavioral states, space use, and resource selection from biotelemetry data collected on both aquatic and terrestrial organisms.



Education
 PhD WFSC (2019) Texas A&M University
 BS BioSci (2013) Clemson University






Prior workshop on animal movement ecology

title: Research
text: I led a project on using mallard telemetry data to investigate the encounter rates and overlap of space use with poultry farms that reported outbreaks of HPAI H5N1 in the Mississippi Flyway.
